      "text": "Triennial | Federal Energy Regulatory CommissionSkip to main content\nFederal Energy Regulatory Commission LogoFERCFederal Energy Regulatory CommissionMobile Menu Button\nFERC\n# Triennial\nThe Commission requires any Seller, which has not been designated a Category 1 Seller for a specific region (and thus are by default Category 2 Sellers in the region), as defined in 18 C.F.R. §35.36, to file updated market power analyses for the regions on an ongoing basis based on a regional review schedule.\nTriennial filings are due in accordance with the schedule established in Appendix D to Order No. 697-A. Pursuant to Order No. 860, after February 1, 2022, Sellers will submit updated market power screens into the MBR Database.\n## When and What to File\nThe Commission requires Category 2 market-based rate Sellers, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36, to file updated market power analyses (Triennials) on an ongoing basis. If a Seller has not been designated as a Category 1 Seller for the specific region in que",
      "highlights": [
        "FERC]\n# Triennial The Commission requires any Seller, which has not been designated a Category 1 Seller for a specific region (and thus are by default Category 2 Sellers in the region), as defined in 18 C.F.R. §35.36, to file updated market power analyses for the regions on an ongoing basis based on a regional review schedule. Triennial filings are due in accordance with the schedule established in Appendix D to Order No. 697-A. Pursuant to Order No. 860, after February 1, 2022, Sellers will submit updated market power screens into the MBR Database.  ...    The Commission requires Category 2 market-based rate Sellers, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36, to file updated market power analyses (Triennials) on an ongoing basis. If a Seller has not been designated as a Category 1 Seller for the specific region in question it is by default Category 2 and must file an updated market power analysis for that region. An entity that has not been designated as a Category 1 Seller for the region must file an analysis even if it does not  ...    power, consistent with 18 C.F.R. §35.37 (b) and (c) (including the indicative study identifiers for the Sellers Market  ...    consistent with 18 C.F.R. §35.37(d) and (e). * The serial number for its asset appendix. The Seller must reference either its most recently created asset appendix,  ...    withOrder No. 697,Order No. 697-A,Order No. 816,Order No. 816-A,Order No. 819, andOrder No. 860. * If the updated market power analysis does not contain revised tariff language, it may be eFiled or submitted by paper. In either case, the indicative screen information must be submitted into the MBR Database. The Commission will review Sellers in each region every three years according to a rotating schedule detailed in Appendix D toOrder No. 697, as revised and corrected in Appendix D, D-1, and D-2 toOrder No. 697-A, andOrder No. 816, Appendix C. * Northwest Region\n* Southwest Region\n* Central Region * Southwest Power Pool\n* Northeast Region