      "text": "Triennial | Federal Energy Regulatory CommissionSkip to main content\nFederal Energy Regulatory Commission LogoFERCFederal Energy Regulatory CommissionMobile Menu Button\nFERC\n# Triennial\nThe Commission requires any Seller, which has not been designated a Category 1 Seller for a specific region (and thus are by default Category 2 Sellers in the region), as defined in 18 C.F.R. §35.36, to file updated market power analyses for the regions on an ongoing basis based on a regional review schedule.\nTriennial filings are due in accordance with the schedule established in Appendix D to Order No. 697-A. Pursuant to Order No. 860, after February 1, 2022, Sellers will submit updated market power screens into the MBR Database.\n## When and What to File\nThe Commission requires Category 2 market-based rate Sellers, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36, to file updated market power analyses (Triennials) on an ongoing basis. If a Seller has not been designated as a Category 1 Seller for the specific region in que",
